cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper involves the use of deep neural networks for image analysis, specifically for extracting tongue contours from ultrasound images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it deals with speech, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep learning models for image analysis also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of automatic labelling algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of neural networks for image analysis suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
